			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The confirmation form template is stored in the file &quot;bbas_config.php&quot; in the variable &quot;$confirmation_page&quot;. Therefore, your steps are:
<br />

<br />
* Get a sample HTML page of your site
<br />
* Put the placeholders &quot;{CHARSET}&quot;, &quot;{TITLE}&quot;, &quot;{EXPLAIN}&quot;, &quot;{QUESTION}&quot;, &quot;{ACTION}&quot;, &quot;{FIELD_ANSWER}&quot;, &quot;{SUBMIT}&quot;, &quot;{HIDDEN_FIELDS}&quot;, &quot;{FOOTNOTE}&quot; into the sample HTML
<br />
* Tune the design
<br />
* Put the HTML code into the file &quot;bbas_config.php&quot;<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
<br />
